&ldquo;Can you tell us about one of your earliest disc golf road trips?&rdquo;
Chains McGraw: &ldquo;Ah, yes. The disc golf road trip. A quintessential American adventure, fueled by adrenaline, questionable substances, and the unyielding thirst for the perfect round. I remember one particular journey, back in &lsquo;76.
I had heard whispers of a course in the wilds of Montana, nestled in the bosom of the Rocky Mountains. A course like no other, they said.
